INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','faq_item',0,6,6,'und',0,'FAQs (or Frequently Asked Questions) display a list of common questions for your site visitors. Clicking any question reveals the answer. FAQs allow site visitors to quickly find answers to their questions without consuming your time. FAQs are a custom content type created by the FAQ feature.</p><p>To add FAQs, click Add content > FAQ.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.drupalgardens.com/learnmore/samplefaq\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>','','safe_html'),('node','workshop',0,26,26,'und',0,'<p><span style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">Putting movement into the body is only the first step as we teach the student to respond to sound thereby giving the student an opportunity to learn the concept of empathy in music. What is often forgotten is the important step of teaching our students how to use movement not as a response but as an actual catalyst to change sound. It is what a conductor should be able to do beyond entrances, exits and tapping out the tempo but more often than not, that is all we really see. It is the same pedagogical sequence as teaching any other musical concept. Experience, Label, Notate. We will do several activities that you can do with your class to help them experience and embody sound. Then we will label the types of movement used and how it can affect sound. Lastly, we will create new sounds and change elements of music with the use of our bodies and movement. This will all be experienced in the context of speech, singing, and playing the Orff Instrumentarium.</span></p>','','safe_html'),('node','bio',0,31,31,'und',0,'<p><span style=\"color: rgb(136, 136, 136); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20.4px;\">Robert de Frece is Professor Emeritus of Music and Music Education at the University of Alberta in Edmonton. Since 1993 he has taught Orff courses all over the United States. He continues to teach in the Orff Schulerk Certifi- cation Program at the University of Alberta. Dr. de Frece is co-author of two music series published by Macmillan/ McGraw-Hill, Share the Music and Spotlight on Music. He has authored many other publications by Alfred Pub- lishing. Dr. de Frece has presented Orff workshops across the United States and Canada and in the People&rsquo;s Republic of China.</span></p>','','safe_html'),('node','bio',0,36,36,'und',0,'<p><strong>Catherine West</strong>&nbsp;is a&nbsp;Toronto Orff Specialist with&nbsp;an international reputation as an author, workshop clinician, course instructor and consultant. She was a member of the National Executive of Carl Orff Canada 2002-14, mostly as the Editor of the national journal, Ostinato. She is the Pedagogy Leader at the Royal Conservatory of Music, where she is also the director and instructor for all levels of Orff teacher training. Additionally, she teaches Orff Levels courses for the Nova Scotia chapter and for Vancouver Community College. Catherine recently completed a term as Instructional Leader in music with the Toronto District School Board, and now works with Smart Start&trade;, a RCM research program investigating the use of music to enhance cognitive skill development in early childhood. She coordinates the Additional Qualifications (teachers&rsquo;) music courses for the University of Toronto&rsquo;s education faculty (OISE) and has worked for numerous clients including the Toronto Symphony Orchestra, The National Arts Centre Orchestra, Opera Lyra Ottawa, Tafelmusik, numerous faculties and boards of education, Orff chapters and conferences, provincial music associations and the Ontario Ministry of Education.</p>','','safe_html'),('node','bio',0,41,41,'und',0,'<p><strong>Susie Green</strong>&nbsp;is an internationally recognized choreographer and master teacher in Dance and Movement Education. She has taught Orff Schulwerk movement Levels I &ndash; III at UBC, Seattle Pacific University and for the past 9 years at Vancouver Community College. She teaches Orff music and movement as an artist in residence at schools in BC, Washington, Finland, Lapland, Moscow, Spain, and Australia. Susie has given workshops at Carl Orff Canada National Conferences, and has been the keynote presenter for AOSA. She has served on the Movement Guideline committees for both COC and AOSA. Susie&nbsp;has received 2 Global Arts Awards -&nbsp;(2002 &amp; 2011) &ldquo;for outstanding contributions to global arts performance and arts education.&rdquo; In addition she received the Commemorative Medal of Canada for &ldquo;contributions to community and country&rdquo;. She continues to work in local and international schools as well as coaching and choreographing. She has sent over 3 dozen students to top jobs in dance companies, Broadway, film and TV. She continues to do Artists in Residencies through ARTSTARTS. Susie inspires students of all ages to recognize and embrace their potential as creative movers.</p>','','safe_html'),('node','course',0,71,71,'und',0,'<p><strong>Certified Levels Courses</strong>&nbsp;are the primary way to receive in-depth training in Orff Schulwerk in Canada, following the guidelines of Carl Orff Canada. They are offered in two-week sessions during the summer, usually running from 8:30 &ndash; 5:00, Monday through Friday. Each Level includes 3 hours of Basic Orff instruction, 1 1/2 hours of Movement, 1 hour of Recorder and 1 hour of Special Topics daily.</p><p><strong>Level I</strong>&nbsp;is a two-week course designed to immerse educators in the learning process of Orff Schulwerk, developing an understanding of this approach to teaching. It includes hands-on training in rhythm, melody, Orff instruments, elemental movement, soprano recorder, Orff theory (pentatonic scales, bordun, ostinati, orchestration for Orff barred instruments), as well as Special Topics sessions. Special Topics sessions may include choral techniques, folk dance, world music traditions, yoga, staging and other topics. Guest teachers will be announced.</p><p><span style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">Successful completion of an approved Level I course with a grade of at least 80% provides participants with the opportunity to continue training in Level II.&nbsp;</span>Enrolment is limited to 24. This course is credited with 4 upper division credits.&nbsp;</p><p><b>REGISTER ONLINE NOW</b></p><p><strong>Please follow the instructions to register online.</strong></p><p><strong>Online Application &amp; Registration Instructions (ORFF 2016 for those who already have a VCC student ID.</strong></p><ul><li>Go to myvcc.ca to login</li><li>Click my services</li><li>Go to step 2 below (Register)</li></ul><p><strong>Online Application &amp; Registration Instructions (ORFF 2016) for new applicants to VCC</strong></p><p><strong>1. Apply</strong></p><ul><li>Enter http://bannerweb.vcc.ca/prod/bwskalog.p_disploginnew in your web browser&nbsp;</li><li>Create a Login ID.</li><li>Create a PIN and enter it again to verify.</li><li>Press Login.&nbsp;</li><li>Select application type (<strong>General Application)</strong> and press continue&nbsp;</li><li>Fill out your application.<ul><li>Select admission term <strong>(General Admission Sept 01, 1997 &ndash; Dec 31, 2099.)</strong></li><li>Fill out your first name and last name</li><li>Press fill out application</li></ul></li><li>Complete Application Checklist<ul><li>Select Name and continue</li><li>Complete each area (a checkmark will appear in the check list once complete&nbsp;</li></ul></li><li>Program selection on your application checklist<ul><li>select<strong> Music Orff</strong></li></ul></li><li>Select <strong>Application is Complete </strong>if there are no error messages or missing information and the application checklist is check marked.&nbsp;</li><li>Select I agree to the terms</li><li>Write down your student number and press access Web for Student or print screen for future reference&nbsp;</li><li>Enter the PIN you created at the beginning of the this process and create new PIN</li><li>Select Continue&nbsp;</li><li>Select security question, answer and press submit</li></ul><p><strong>2. Register</strong></p><ul><li>Select <strong>Student Services</strong>.&nbsp;</li><li>Select <strong>Register For Courses</strong>.</li><li>Select <strong>Add/Drop Classes</strong>.&nbsp;</li><li>Select Term <strong>Spring/Summer 2016&hellip;. </strong>May 1, 2016 &ndash; Aug 31, 2016 and press submit</li><li><strong>Add Classes</strong>, enter one of the CRN numbers below and press submit</li></ul><p><strong>Orff Teacher Training Level 1 &ndash; CRN 61377</strong></p><p><strong>Orff Teacher Training Level 2 - CRN 61378</strong></p><ul><li>Select <strong>Fee Payment and submit</strong></li><li>Select<strong> PAY NOW </strong>and follow payment instructions to&nbsp;complete your registration</li></ul><p><strong>If you have any questions about how to register please call or email:</strong></p><p><strong>Maria Gutierrez</strong><br />Admissions Clerk -&nbsp;Registrar&rsquo;s Office,<br />Broadway Campus -&nbsp;Vancouver, BC<br /><strong>(ph)&nbsp; 604-871-7000 ext. 7038</strong><br />(fax)&nbsp; 604-871-7458<br /><strong>ro@vcc.ca</strong><br />&nbsp;<br /><strong>*Fee: Breakdown&nbsp;</strong><br /><strong>Domestic Students *</strong>NOTE: Fees are subject to change and you will be required to pay any increase.<br />Application Fee: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$35.00<br />Tuition: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $827.00<br />Student Union Fee: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$29.36<br />College Initiative Fee:&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$9.88<br />Campus Resource Fee: $16.54<br />Total Cost:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Level 1 = $917.68<br />Total Cost:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Level 2&nbsp;= $917.68&nbsp; &nbsp;<br /><strong>International Students&nbsp;</strong>*International students must purchase medical insurance available for $2/day **NOTE: Fees are subject to change and you will be required to pay any increase.<br />Application Fee &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$135.00<br />Tuition: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $1271.00<br />Student Union Fee:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;$29.36<br />College Initiative Fee:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;$9.88<br />Campus Resource Fee:&nbsp;$12.71<br />Total Cost:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Level 1 = $1457.95<br />Total Cost:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Level 2&nbsp;= $1457.95&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>','','full_html'),('node','bio',0,81,81,'und',0,'<p><strong>Pam Hetrick</strong>&nbsp;has taught music for over 30 years and is currently an Orff music specialist in Burnaby. She presents Orff Schulwerk workshops frequently in the U.S. and Canada, including National Conferences in both countries. She is Past Co-President of the BC Orff Chapter and served on the American Orff Schulwerk Editorial Board for 10 years. Pam has studied music in Bali, Indonesia, music and dance in Madras, India and was a recipient of the American Gunild Keetman Grant for research on Balinese Tingklik. Performing experience includes steel drum bands, Gamelan Sekar Jaya with whom she toured Indonesia twice, Keith Terry Body Music Ensemble, and currently Adanu Habobo, an African music and dance ensemble. She taught Level 1 at Western Oregon University for two summers and is currently Course Director and Level I Instructor for the Orff Teacher Training Program at Vancouver Community College for its 9th&nbsp;year. Pam received the 2014 BCMEA Music Educator Award.</p>','','safe_html'),('node','page',0,86,86,'und',0,'<h2>Birthe Kulich Scholarship</h2><p> Application Deadline: May 15th</p><p>This scholarship is offered each year to one or more undergraduate or newly graduated students with a Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree who are&nbsp;members in good standing of the BC Orff Chapter. If there are no applicants with this criteria, then a graduate student will be considered. The award may be used for Orff Intro or Orff Level I. Level II applicants will also be considered.</p><p>Applicants should apply directly to the&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:pastpresident@bcorff.ca\">Past President</a>&nbsp;with&nbsp;<span style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">a letter of intent, transcript, and a letter of recommendation.</span></p><h2>&nbsp;</h2><h2>Gunild Keetman Scholarship</h2><p><span style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\"> Application Deadline: April 15th</span></p><p>The Gunild Keetman Scholarships are awarded in the spring of each year and are available for all approved Orff Schulwerk courses offered in Canada, summer and winter.</p><p>Applicants must be members in good standing of Carl Orff Canada, who have successfully completed a Level I Orff course.</p><p><span style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">For more information&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">visit:&nbsp;</span><a href=\"http://www.orffcanada.ca/scholarships.html\" style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">Carl Orff Canada</a></p><h2>&nbsp;</h2><h2>The Joe Berarducci Scholarship</h2><p>Application Deadline: May 15th</p><p>A scholarship of up to $500, in honour of Joe Berarducci, is awarded to one or more&nbsp;applicants, who are members in good standing of the BC Orff Chapter,&nbsp;with priority given in the following&nbsp;order:<br /><br />&bull; applicants training under the Carl Orff Canada Mentorship Program for Levels Course Instructors<br />&bull; applicants&nbsp;who are&nbsp;enrolled in an accredited Level III Orff Course<br />&bull; applicants who have already completed Orff Level III and who are&nbsp;enrolled in an accredited Post Level III Master Class</p><p>This scholarship will be paid upon completion of the class for which it is awarded.</p><p><span style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">Applicants should apply directly to the&nbsp;</span><a href=\"mailto:pastpresident@bcorff.ca\" style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">Past President</a><span style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">&nbsp;with&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">a letter of intent&nbsp;and a letter of recommendation.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2>The Carolyn McMillan Research Grant</h2><p><span style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">Application deadline: June 15th</span></p><p>Established in 1994, this $1000 grant is offered to encourage research relating to the application and study of Orff Schulwerk in Canada. Projects may be broad-based and may include such topics as:<br /><br />&bull; practical applications for the classroom<br />&bull; the integration of the Orff approach in music therapy, private teaching, geriatrics, palliative care etc.<br />&bull; pilot projects for the music education major or the practising teacher<br />&bull; a descriptive and evaluative annotation of bibliographic resources on Orff philosophy and/or Orff materials&nbsp;<br /><br />Applicants must be current members of Carl Orff Canada, Canadian citizens and Level III graduates.</p><p>For more information&nbsp;<span style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">visit:&nbsp;</span><a href=\"http://www.orffcanada.ca/scholarships.html\" style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">Carl Orff Canada</a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2>The Deborah Kerr Scholarship</h2><p><span style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">Application deadline: One month prior to Children&#39;s Day</span></p><p>This scholarship is offered to&nbsp;student participants&nbsp;of<span style=\"line-height: 1.;\">&nbsp;Children&#39;s Day. A limited number of scholarships are available for students that have financial need and are recommended by their teacher. </span></p><p><span style=\"line-height: 1.;\">Teachers should a</span><span style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">pply directly to the&nbsp;</span><a href=\"mailto:pastpresident@bcorff.ca\" style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">Past President</a><span style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">&nbsp;on behalf of their students.</span></p>','','safe_html'),('node','page',0,91,91,'und',0,'<h2>Adopt an Orffan !</h2><p>Do you have an extra room to host a BC Orff Chapter member from out of town? Want to attend a BC Orff Chapter workshop in the Lower Mainland but have no place to stay?  Contact Vanessa Fer at v.fer@hotmail.com</p><h2>Billeting Policy</h2><p>The purpose of this policy is to set guidelines and suggestions for both the host and the guest. We, the BC Orff Chapter, will try to arrange billeting so that people who come from out of town may attend our workshops without the added expense of a hotel stay.<br />Both the host and the guest must agree to the terms prior to the home stay.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;The guest will pay the host $30.00 per night.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;For this remuneration the host will provide the guest with a private bedroom and use of a washroom facility.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;All other provisions such as food, use of kitchen facilities, computer, telephone, and transportation are at the discretion of the host. These items should be clarified and arranged in advance of the stay so that there is no uncertainty or assumptions from either party.</p>','','safe_html'),('node','page',0,96,96,'und',0,'<p>To join the BC Orff Chapter, become a member of Carl Orff Canada. Please reg<span style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">ister online at the&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://www.regonline.com/register/checkin.aspx?MethodId=0&amp;eventsessionId=ac4ec0869c484dfa856d0b1a2658df21&amp;eventID=1120594\" style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">COC Online registration system</a>.</p><p>If you are experiencing difficulty with&nbsp;online registration,&nbsp;please email the&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:membership@bcorff.ca\">Membership Secretary</a>.</p><p><strong>Membership fees:</strong></p><ul><li>Regular Member ($60 per year)</li><li>Student Member ($30 per year, you must be a full time student to qualify)</li><li>Retired Member ($40 per year)</li></ul><p><strong><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 15.6px; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\">Benefits of membership include:</span></strong></p><ul><li><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 15.6px; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\">Membership in Carl Orff Canada</span></li><li><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 15.6px; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 15.6px; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\">Discounts on Chapter Workshops</span></span></li><li><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 15.6px; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\">Free admission to Sharing Sessions and Children&#39;s Day</span></li><li><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 15.6px; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 15.6px; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 15.6px; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\">Subscription to <em>Ostinato</em>, the journal of Carl Orff Canada</span></span></span></li><li><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 15.6px; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 15.6px; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 15.6px; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 15.6px; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\">Access to the Chapter Library</span></span></span></span></li><li><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 15.6px; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 15.6px; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 15.6px; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 15.6px; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 15.6px; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\">Scholarships for Teacher Education Courses&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span></li></ul>','','safe_html'),('node','page',0,101,101,'und',0,'<p>Based on the ideas of Carl Orff and Gunild Keetman, Orff Schulwerk has taken root around the world, inspiring teachers globally. This child-centred approach to music and movement education encourages creativity and play, where the enjoyment of group music making, improvisation, and composition are the focus. Using speech, movement, singing, and child-accessible instruments Orff Schulwerk advocates teaching that relies on the creativity, imagination and musicianship of the teacher.</p><p>Orff training is available through <a href=\"workshops/bc-orff\">workshops</a>&nbsp;and <a href=\"courses\">teacher education courses</a>&nbsp;including an <a href=\"node/201\">Introduction to&nbsp;Orff Schulwerk</a>, <a href=\"node/71\">Level I</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"node/191\">Level II</a>, <a href=\"node/196\">Level&nbsp;III</a>, and <a href=\"node/211\">Post Level III courses</a>. The BC Orff Chapter also offers opportunities for&nbsp;profession development through member Sharing Sessions and Chidren&#39;s Day events.&nbsp;Understanding and implementing the Orff philosophy of creative education is a lifetime pursuit, requiring the experience of teaching children while taking the courses to understand and implement the ideas.</p><p>The BC Orff Chapter is committed to providing these opportunities for teachers.</p>','','safe_html'),('node','news',0,166,166,'und',0,'<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm\">On September 19<sup>th</sup>, 2015, the BC Orff Chapter celebrated it&rsquo;s 40<sup>th</sup> birthday. The day was kicked started with an exciting full day workshop with master teachers, Joe Berrarducci, Leanne Roy and Susie Green. After the workshop present, past and new Orff members gathered in local restaurant for some laughs and celebratory toasts.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm\"><b>The BC Orff Chapter has a lot to be proud of!</b></p>','On September 19th, 2015, the BC Orff Chapter celebrated it’s 40th birthday. The day was kicked started with an exciting full day workshop with master teachers, Joe Berrarducci, Leanne Roy and Susie Green. ','safe_html'),('node','resource',0,176,176,'und',0,'<p>Children&#39;s Day 2014</p><p><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/XUzx6GsdL0E\" width=\"560\"></iframe></p>','<p><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"189\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/XUzx6GsdL0E\" width=\"336\"></iframe></p>','full_html'),('node','resource',0,181,181,'und',0,'<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm\">[[{\"type\":\"media\",\"view_mode\":\"media_crop\",\"fid\":\"81\",\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"\",\"class\":\"media-image\",\"id\":\"media_crop_4554444819223\",\"media_crop_h\":\"0\",\"media_crop_image_style\":\"large\",\"media_crop_instance\":\"1\",\"media_crop_rotate\":\"0\",\"media_crop_scale_h\":\"0\",\"media_crop_scale_w\":\"0\",\"media_crop_w\":\"0\",\"media_crop_x\":\"0\",\"media_crop_y\":\"0\",\"typeof\":\"foaf:Image\"}}]]</p><!--break--><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm\"><em>Teach the A section - Pat part &ndash; rhythm syllables helped</em></p><ul><li><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm\"><em>with children&hellip; focus on one of the rhythmic units</em></p></li></ul><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm\"><em>When secure add the Clap part</em></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm\"><em>Continue adding parts&hellip; until secure</em></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm\"><em>Transfer to BP parts&hellip; perform</em></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm\"><em>B section became improvisation in small groups&hellip;.. BP</em></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm\"><em>C section was non-pitched instruments</em></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm\"><em>Brought it to some form of final production for the session</em></p>','','full_html'),('node','bio',0,186,186,'und',0,'<p>Dr. Adam Jonathan Con is Assistant Professor of Music at University of Victoria School of Music. Conductor of the UVic Chorus, he also teaches Secondary Choral Rehearsal Techniques and Literature, Middle and Elementary School choir methods, Elementary Music Methods, Music Education Foundation, Choral Conducting, and supervises music education students. He is certified in Orff Schulwerk and embodies the philosophy in every aspect of music education at all levels. He previously served in both Choral Activities and in Music Education at the Bob Cole Conservatory of Music, California State University, Long Beach, at Wittenberg University in Springfield, Ohio and at Georgia Southern University in Statesboro, Georgia. A native of Vancouver, he earned his Bachelor&rsquo;s and Master Degree in Music Education from the University of British Columbia. At the Florida State University, he earned a Doctorate of Philosophy in Music Education (Choral Conducting Emphasis) studying with Rodney Eichenberger, Andre Thomas, Clifford Madsen and Judy Bowers. In addition, Dr. Con has extensive study experience as a Tai Chi Chuan and Alexander Technique practitioner.</p><p>In high demand in the United States and Canada both as a clinician, guest conductor and choral conducting teacher, Dr. Con has been invited to present and conduct at prestigious events such as the Canadian and American National Orff-Schulwerk Conferences, Podium: the Canadian National Choral Conducting Symposium, the Canadian National GALA Conference, the Alberta Provincial Music Educator&rsquo;s Conference, the British Columbia Provincial Music Educator&rsquo;s Conference, the British Columbia Choral Federation, the British Columbia Kodaly Society, the Ohio State Music Educator&rsquo;s Conference, the Georgia and California State American Choral Directors Association Conference, and the Georgia Music Educator&rsquo;s Conference. His talent and ability to work with all levels of musical experience is grounded in 15 years of diverse K-12 public school music teaching in British Columbia which includes Orff, Kodály, and Dalcroze based general music, French immersion music, middle and secondary school choral, vocal jazz, concert band and jazz band. His professional conducting experiences include numerous All-State and honor choirs, civic orchestras, professional musical theatre, community choirs, concert bands, and 36 years as a church choir director and organist. &nbsp;</p>','','full_html'),('node','course',0,191,191,'und',0,'<p style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\"><strong>Certified Levels Courses</strong>&nbsp;are the primary way to receive in-depth training in Orff Schulwerk in Canada, following the guidelines of Carl Orff Canada. They are offered in two-week sessions during the summer, usually running from 8:30 &ndash; 5:00, Monday through Friday. Each Level includes 3 hours of Basic Orff instruction, 1 1/2 hours of Movement, 1 hour of Recorder and 1 hour of Special Topics daily.</p><p style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\"><strong>Level II&nbsp;</strong>is a two-week course where students consolidate the learning that occurred in Level I as well as explore compound meters, hybrid meters and diatonic melodies and accompaniments as well as extended forms, through playing, improvising and composing. Students will demonstrate fluency with the transfer process in teaching a lesson to their peers. Recorder will include continuation of soprano recorder as well as introduction of the alto recorder. Students will join Level I and Level III for Special Topics each day.</p><p style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">Successful completion of an approved Level II course with a grade of at least 80% provides participants with the opportunity to continue training in Level III. This course is credited with 4 upper division credits.</p><p style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\"><b>REGISTER ONLINE NOW</b></p><p style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\"><strong>Please follow the instructions to register online.</strong></p><p style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\"><strong>Online Application &amp; Registration Instructions (ORFF 2016 for those who already have a VCC student ID.</strong></p><ul style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\"><li>Go to myvcc.ca to login</li><li>Click my services</li><li>Go to step 2 below (Register)</li></ul><p style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\"><strong>Online Application &amp; Registration Instructions (ORFF 2016) for new applicants to VCC</strong></p><p style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\"><strong>1. Apply</strong></p><ul style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\"><li>Enter http://bannerweb.vcc.ca/prod/bwskalog.p_disploginnew in your web browser&nbsp;</li><li>Create a Login ID.</li><li>Create a PIN and enter it again to verify.</li><li>Press Login.&nbsp;</li><li>Select application type (<strong>General Application)</strong>&nbsp;and press continue&nbsp;</li><li>Fill out your application.<ul><li>Select admission term&nbsp;<strong>(General Admission Sept 01, 1997 &ndash; Dec 31, 2099.)</strong></li><li>Fill out your first name and last name</li><li>Press fill out application</li></ul></li><li>Complete Application Checklist<ul><li>Select Name and continue</li><li>Complete each area (a checkmark will appear in the check list once complete&nbsp;</li></ul></li><li>Program selection on your application checklist<ul><li>select<strong>&nbsp;Music Orff</strong></li></ul></li><li>Select&nbsp;<strong>Application is Complete&nbsp;</strong>if there are no error messages or missing information and the application checklist is check marked.&nbsp;</li><li>Select I agree to the terms</li><li>Write down your student number and press access Web for Student or print screen for future reference&nbsp;</li><li>Enter the PIN you created at the beginning of the this process and create new PIN</li><li>Select Continue&nbsp;</li><li>Select security question, answer and press submit</li></ul><p style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\"><strong>2. Register</strong></p><ul style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\"><li>Select&nbsp;<strong>Student Services</strong>.&nbsp;</li><li>Select&nbsp;<strong>Register For Courses</strong>.</li><li>Select&nbsp;<strong>Add/Drop Classes</strong>.&nbsp;</li><li>Select Term&nbsp;<strong>Spring/Summer 2016&hellip;.&nbsp;</strong>May 1, 2016 &ndash; Aug 31, 2016 and press submit</li><li><strong>Add Classes</strong>, enter one of the CRN numbers below and press submit</li></ul><p style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\"><strong>Orff Teacher Training Level 1 &ndash; CRN 61377</strong></p><p style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\"><strong>Orff Teacher Training Level 2 - CRN 61378</strong></p><ul style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\"><li>Select&nbsp;<strong>Fee Payment and submit</strong></li><li>Select<strong>&nbsp;PAY NOW&nbsp;</strong>and follow payment instructions to&nbsp;complete your registration</li></ul><p style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\"><strong>If you have any questions about how to register please call or email:</strong></p><p style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\"><strong>Maria Gutierrez</strong><br />Admissions Clerk -&nbsp;Registrar&rsquo;s Office,<br />Broadway Campus -&nbsp;Vancouver, BC<br /><strong>(ph)&nbsp; 604-871-7000 ext. 7038</strong><br />(fax)&nbsp; 604-871-7458<br /><strong>ro@vcc.ca</strong><br />&nbsp;<br /><strong>*Fee: Breakdown&nbsp;</strong><br /><strong>Domestic Students *</strong>NOTE: Fees are subject to change and you will be required to pay any increase.<br />Application Fee: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$35.00<br />Tuition: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $827.00<br />Student Union Fee: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$29.36<br />College Initiative Fee:&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$9.88<br />Campus Resource Fee: $16.54<br />Total Cost:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Level 1 = $917.68<br />Total Cost:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Level 2&nbsp;= $917.68&nbsp; &nbsp;<br /><strong>International Students&nbsp;</strong>*International students must purchase medical insurance available for $2/day **NOTE: Fees are subject to change and you will be required to pay any increase.<br />Application Fee &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$135.00<br />Tuition: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $1271.00<br />Student Union Fee:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;$29.36<br />College Initiative Fee:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;$9.88<br />Campus Resource Fee:&nbsp;$12.71<br />Total Cost:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Level 1 = $1457.95<br />Total Cost:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Level 2&nbsp;= $1457.95 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>','','full_html'),('node','course',0,196,196,'und',0,'<p>Level III is not being offered this year but is planned to be offered in 2017. Please contact Pam Hetrick if you are interested in taking this course or if you would like further information.</p>','','full_html'),('node','course',0,201,201,'und',0,'<p>This course provides a foundation in Orff Schulwerk and offers insights into bringing music and dance into the daily life of children. It is designed to give music specialists and those who can read and write music an introduction to the many elements which comprise the Orff philosophy of music education. Explore a creative approach that integrates speech, singing, movement, improvisation and instrument technique on pitched and non-pitched percussion instruments as well as recorder.</p><p>Full attendance is strongly encouraged. Participants who miss a day of instruction will only earn a certificate once they have registered for and completed&nbsp;a full day workshop with the BC Orff Chapter.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>','','full_html'),('node','bio',0,206,206,'und',0,'<p><strong>Cathy Bayley</strong>&nbsp;has taught elementary school music, Kindergarten to Grade 7 in Canada and Australia and is retired from her position as the Fine Arts Coordinator for the Surrey School District with responsibilities in dance, drama, visual arts and music from Kindergarten to Grade 12. Cathy has Orff Schulwerk Levels I, II and III and Post Level III as well as a Diploma in Visual and Performing Arts from UBC. She has a Masters of Education from the University of Victoria. She is passionate about the Orff approach to music education and has worked for many years to promote this philosophy both locally and nationally, conducting workshops all over British Columbia. She has served as President of Carl Orff Canada. In addition, she is the 2014 recipient of the BCMEA Elementary Professional Music Educator Award.</p>','','full_html'),('node','course',0,211,211,'und',0,'<p class=\"p1\"><b>Into the Woods! Finding the Orff Forest amongst the Trees </b></p><p class=\"p1\"><b>Presented by Catherine West</b></p><p class=\"p1\">An Orff lesson takes a learner on a magical pathway through a musical forest, inviting us to explore and even select our own direction, finally arriving safely at a creative end point which makes sense of the learning journey. As Orff teachers we can access many wonderful individual elements &ndash; our &ldquo;trees&rdquo;: those of musical style, curriculum, Orff Process, Orff Media, the Volumes, children&rsquo;s games, traditional music of Canada and other places, western art music, to mention only a few, all growing from rich musical roots. Add in cross-curricular connections to social studies, sciences, math and other subjects and the choices are truly beyond measure. But how can we plan with so many desirables and mandates? This master-class will help teachers to identify the vision, the big picture &ldquo;forest&rdquo; and to populate it with a selection of wonderful, appropriately chosen, &ldquo;trees.&rdquo;</p><p class=\"p1\"><strong>Experience</strong></p><ul class=\"ul1\"><li class=\"li1\">classroom-tested units for K-6 classes&nbsp;</li><li class=\"li1\">the magic and delight of the original Orff materials and sequence&nbsp;</li><li class=\"li1\">repertoire and activities from different times and places</li><li class=\"li1\">Orff instruments, percussion, and recorder</li><li class=\"li1\">moving, singing, listening and playing&nbsp;</li></ul><p class=\"p1\"><strong>Bring&nbsp;</strong></p><ul class=\"ul1\"><li class=\"li1\">expectations, literature, masterworks of art or dance, themes, repertoire, instruments you would like to connect to your music curriculum next year</li></ul><p class=\"p1\"><strong>Create</strong></p><ul class=\"ul1\"><li class=\"li1\">mini-units which prioritize key learnings but do not neglect the rich possibilities for other connections&nbsp;</li></ul><p class=\"li1\">&nbsp;</p><p class=\"li1\">&nbsp;</p>','','full_html'),('node','news',0,221,221,'und',0,'<p>[[{\"type\":\"media\",\"view_mode\":\"media_crop\",\"fid\":\"171\",\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"\",\"class\":\"media-image\",\"id\":\"media_crop_872822562232\",\"media_crop_h\":\"0\",\"media_crop_image_style\":\"large\",\"media_crop_instance\":\"11\",\"media_crop_rotate\":\"0\",\"media_crop_scale_h\":\"0\",\"media_crop_scale_w\":\"0\",\"media_crop_w\":\"0\",\"media_crop_x\":\"0\",\"media_crop_y\":\"0\",\"typeof\":\"foaf:Image\"}}]]</p><p>Carl Orff Canada National Conference 2016<br />April 28 - May 1<br />Saskatoon, SK</p><p>Register Now!</p><p><a href=\"https://sites.google.com/site/bridges2016orff/home\">https://sites.google.com/site/bridges2016orff/home</a></p>','','full_html'),('node','news',0,226,226,'und',0,'<p><span style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">The BC Orff Chapter&nbsp;has&nbsp;created a new policy</span>&nbsp;to assist our members who live outside the Lower Mainland and encourage them to attend our workshops:</p><p>All BC Orff Workshops held in the Lower Mainland&nbsp;are <strong>free</strong> to members living north of Squamish, east of Abbotsford, on Vancouver Island, the Gulf Islands or the Sunshine Coast. Any member&nbsp;wishing to take advantage of this policy must contact the Membership Secretary (membership@bcorff.ca)&nbsp;at least one week prior to the workshop.</p>','The BC Orff Chapter has created a new policy to assist our members who live outside the Lower Mainland and encourage them to attend our workshops:','full_html'),('node','page',0,231,231,'und',0,'<p><strong>GENERAL INFORMATION</strong></p><p>Based on the ideas of Carl Orff and Gunild Keetman, Orff Schulwerk has taken root around the world, inspiring teachers globally. This child-centred approach to music and movement education encourages creativity and play, where the enjoyment of group music making, improvisation, and composition are the focus. Using speech, movement, singing, and child-accessible instruments Orff Schulwerk advocates teaching that relies on the creativity, imagination and musicianship of the teacher.</p><p>Orff training is available through workshops, Introductory Courses, Level Courses, and Post Level III Courses. Understanding and implementing the Orff philosophy of creative education is a lifetime pursuit, requiring the experience of teaching children while taking the courses to understand and implement the ideas.</p><p>The BC Orff Chapter is committed to providing these opportunities for teachers.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>ORFF SCHULWERK CERTIFICATION PROGRAM August 8 &ndash; 19, 2016</strong></p><p>Vancouver Community College, Downtown Campus, Vancouver, BC</p><p>Contact Pam Hetrick</p><p>levels@bcorff.ca</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Certified Levels Courses</strong> are the primary way to receive in-depth training in Orff Schulwerk in Canada, following the guidelines of Carl Orff Canada. They are offered in two-week sessions during the summer, usually running from 8:30 &ndash; 5, Monday through Friday. Each Level includes 3 hours of Basic Orff instruction, 1 1/2 hours of Movement, 1 hour of Recorder and 1 hour of Special Topics daily. Please refer to categories under &ldquo;Orff Training&rdquo; for content specific to each Level.</p><p>Orff Level Training is available every summer at Vancouver Community College Downtown Campus 250 West Pender, Vancouver, at the corner of Hamilton and Dunsmuir across from the Vancouver Playhouse (Stadium Skytrain).</p><p>Each Level (I, II, III) is 4 upper division credits and is accepted by the Teacher Qualification Service. Introduction to Orff Schulwerk is a non-credit course.</p><p>It is expected that students will take at least a year between each Level in order to begin to absorb and implement training through their teaching during the year. After successful completion of Levels I, II, and III teachers are awarded Orff Schulwerk Certification.</p><p><em>These Courses are endorsed by Carl Orff Canada.</em></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Student comments from past Level Training Courses at VCC:</strong></p><blockquote><p>This course has literally blown me away; I have had a whole paradigm shift in how to approach my teaching.</p></blockquote><blockquote><p>This course has come nothing short of revolutionizing my approach to music and children.</p></blockquote><blockquote><p>The goals I set were exceeded by day two in this course!</p></blockquote><blockquote><p>There is NOTHING like divine revelation, and it wouldn&#39;t be an overstatement to suggest that this experience has been a revelation for me.</p></blockquote><blockquote><p>For the past 2 weeks I have been in the trenches of learning the most amazing musical process I could have ever imagined.</p></blockquote><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>The Faculty</strong></p><p>Pam Hetrick &ndash; Course Director, Level I</p><p>Catherine West &ndash; Level II</p><p>Susie Green &ndash; Movement I, II</p>','','full_html'),('node','paypal_button',0,236,236,'und',0,'<form action=\"https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr\" method=\"post\" target=\"_top\"><input name=\"cmd\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"_s-xclick\" /> <input name=\"hosted_button_id\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"JM4BVFJGHZF7W\" /> <input alt=\"PayPal - The safer, easier way to pay online!\" border=\"0\" name=\"submit\" src=\"https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/btn/btn_paynow_SM.gif\" type=\"image\" /> <img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" height=\"1\" src=\"https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/scr/pixel.gif\" width=\"1\" /></form>','','full_html'),('node','paypal_button',0,241,241,'und',0,'<form action=\"https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr\" method=\"post\" target=\"_top\"><input name=\"cmd\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"_s-xclick\" /> <input name=\"hosted_button_id\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"2N5FNXCGXRFCN\" /> <input alt=\"PayPal - The safer, easier way to pay online!\" border=\"0\" name=\"submit\" src=\"https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/btn/btn_paynow_SM.gif\" type=\"image\" /> <img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" height=\"1\" src=\"https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/scr/pixel.gif\" width=\"1\" /></form>','','full_html'),('node','paypal_button',0,246,246,'und',0,'<form action=\"https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr\" method=\"post\" target=\"_top\"><input name=\"cmd\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"_s-xclick\" /> <input name=\"hosted_button_id\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"L9ACHU4PSTX5G\" 