ng: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: medium;\">Regular&nbsp;Course&nbsp;Fee:&nbsp;$400&nbsp;</p><p id=\"yui_3_16_0_ym19_1_1464452417341_6819\" style=\"-webkit-padding-start: 0px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: medium;\">&nbsp;</p><p id=\"yui_3_16_0_ym19_1_1464452417341_6821\" style=\"-webkit-padding-start: 0px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"-webkit-padding-start: 0px; font-size: 12pt;\">Phone:&nbsp;(780)&nbsp;882‐7988 &nbsp;&nbsp;</span>Toll&nbsp;Free:&nbsp;1‐800‐864‐4140 &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style=\"-webkit-padding-start: 0px; font-size: 12pt;\">Fax:&nbsp;(780)&nbsp;882‐7908&nbsp;</span></p><p id=\"yui_3_16_0_ym19_1_1464452417341_6823\" style=\"-webkit-padding-start: 0px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: medium;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ***NRLC&nbsp;office&nbsp;closes&nbsp;June&nbsp;28th&nbsp;at&nbsp;noon***&nbsp;</p><p id=\"yui_3_16_0_ym19_1_1464452417341_6825\" style=\"-webkit-padding-start: 0px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"-webkit-padding-start: 0px; font-size: 12pt;\">A</span><span style=\"-webkit-padding-start: 0px; font-size: 12pt;\">fter&nbsp;June&nbsp;28th,&nbsp;please&nbsp;contact: &nbsp;</span>Course&nbsp;Facilitator:&nbsp;&nbsp;Laura&nbsp;Storey &nbsp;</p><p id=\"yui_3_16_0_ym19_1_1464452417341_6827\" style=\"-webkit-padding-start: 0px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: medium;\">Home:&nbsp;(780)&nbsp;568‐2291 &nbsp;Cell:&nbsp;(780)&nbsp;876‐6108 E‐Mail:&nbsp;roynlaura@persona.ca&nbsp;</p>','','full_html'),('node','bio',0,301,301,'und',0,'<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Debra Giebelhaus‐Maloney</strong> is a&nbsp;Canadian Orff leader, clinician, teacher&nbsp;trainer, educator, a past president of <i>Carl&nbsp;Orff Canada, </i>and&nbsp;a child advocate&nbsp;committed to excellence in music education.&nbsp;Holder of a B.FA, B.Ed, and M.Ed, Debra&rsquo;s&nbsp;current role as a consultant includes&nbsp;designing and developing music, drama,&nbsp;language, arts‐infused ELL programs, sensory&nbsp;and cross‐curricular programs for school&nbsp;boards, universities, and music organizations&nbsp;internationally.&nbsp;Debra adjudicates choral, drama and speech&nbsp;arts, provides professional development for&nbsp;teachers and delivers <i>Artist in Residency</i>&nbsp;programs for students from preschool to&nbsp;Grade 12.&nbsp;Two of&nbsp;Debra&rsquo;s commissions include <i>Listen to&nbsp;the Children</i>, a compilation of English and&nbsp;Inuktitut children&rsquo;s stories written with the&nbsp;children in <i>Nunavik, Quebec </i>and a series of&nbsp;four early childhood children&rsquo;s concerts for&nbsp;the&nbsp;<i>California Orange County Pacific&nbsp;Symphony </i>and <i>Youth Orchestra.</i>&nbsp;Debra founded &ldquo;<i>Orff at </i>SING MOVE PLAY&rdquo;, a&nbsp;music education program for 3‐9 year olds&nbsp;that continues to thrive and is the inspiration&nbsp;for much of her storytelling and game&nbsp;development, some of which can be found in&nbsp;her book, <i>Music and Language Circle Games.</i></p>','','full_html'),('node','news',0,306,306,'und',0,'<h2 style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\"><strong>REGISTER ONLINE NOW</strong></h2><p style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\"><strong>REGISTER BY JULY 1st to ensure courses will have sufficient enrollment to run!</strong></p><p style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\"><strong>Please follow the instructions to register online for Orff Levels I and II at Vancouver Community College.</strong></p><p style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\"><a href=\"/course/level-i-orff-schulwerk-certification-program\"><u><strong>Level I - Orff Schulwerk Certification Program</strong></u></a></p><p style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\"><a href=\"/course/level-ii-orff-schulwerk-certification-program\"><u><strong>Level II - Orff Schulwerk Certification Program</strong></u></a></p><p style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">&nbsp;</p>','REGISTER BY JULY 1st \r\nto ensure courses will have sufficient enrollment to run!\r\n\r\nSummer Levels Courses at VCC! August 8 - 19, 2016\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','full_html'),('node','page',0,311,311,'und',0,'<p>This is a place to upload the yearly brochure. The page does not need to be published. To update the brochure that is linked in the &quot;Download our current brochure&quot; button, upload a new file to the files field below. Then drag the new file to the top of the list of files and save (&quot;Save&quot; button at the bottom &nbsp;of the page). The first file in the list will be used for the button.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Technical note: The button is output by a views block: the &quot;brochure&quot; view displays only the first file of this node.</p>','','full_html'),('node','news',0,316,316,'und',0,'<p>[[{\"type\":\"media\",\"view_mode\":\"media_crop\",\"fid\":\"281\",\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"\",\"class\":\"media-image\",\"id\":\"media_crop_7890078899386\",\"media_crop_h\":\"0\",\"media_crop_image_style\":\"large\",\"media_crop_instance\":\"26\",\"media_crop_rotate\":\"90\",\"media_crop_scale_h\":\"0\",\"media_crop_scale_w\":\"0\",\"media_crop_w\":\"0\",\"media_crop_x\":\"0\",\"media_crop_y\":\"0\",\"style\":\"height: 600px; width: 450px;\",\"typeof\":\"foaf:Image\"}}]]</p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: normal;\">BC Orff Co-Presidents Sonja Karlson and Vanessa Fer enter with the BC banner at the Bridges opening ceremonies.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>[[{\"type\":\"media\",\"view_mode\":\"media_crop\",\"fid\":\"286\",\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"\",\"class\":\"media-image\",\"id\":\"media_crop_5470347511671\",\"media_crop_h\":\"0\",\"media_crop_image_style\":\"large\",\"media_crop_instance\":\"31\",\"media_crop_rotate\":\"90\",\"media_crop_scale_h\":\"0\",\"media_crop_scale_w\":\"0\",\"media_crop_w\":\"0\",\"media_crop_x\":\"0\",\"media_crop_y\":\"0\",\"style\":\"height: 600px; width: 450px;\",\"typeof\":\"foaf:Image\"}}]]</p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"-webkit-padding-start: 0px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: normal;\">&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\" id=\"yui_3_16_0_ym19_1_1464498152916_5181\" style=\"-webkit-padding-start: 0px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: normal;\">The BC Orff Chapter contingent at Bridges 2016, the National Conference of Carl Orff Canada:</p><p dir=\"ltr\" id=\"yui_3_16_0_ym19_1_1464498152916_5099\" style=\"-webkit-padding-start: 0px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: normal;\">(L-R) &nbsp;Vanessa Fer, Sherryl Sewepagaham, Brenda di Rezze, Sonja Karlson, Laureen Schellenberg, Jan Nordstrand, Angie Lundin. &nbsp;Missing: &nbsp;Samantha Guglielmucci.</p>','View memories from Bridges, this year\'s National Conference.','full_html'),('node','bio',0,321,321,'und',0,'<p><strong>Judith Hirsch</strong> recently moved to British Columbia, Canada from Austria. She studied Elemental Music and Dance Education at the Orff-Institute, University Mozarteum in Salzburg. She also studied Experimental and Contemporary Dance at SEAD (Salzburg Experimental Academy of Dance) and studied drums and percussion at the University Mozarteum for 4 years. Judith has appeared in several performances as a dancer, percussionist and choreographer. She teaches body percussion, voice percussion, trash percussion, drums, connection of music-voice-dance, dance technique, dance improvisation and dance composition. Her target groups are kids from the age of 7-18, students in education and adults. She has presented extensively in Europe and now in Canada.</p>','','full_html'),('node','bio',0,326,326,'und',0,'<p><strong>Sherryl Sewepagaham</strong> is Cree-Dene from northern Alberta and is an experienced Elementary Music Teacher. She earned a Level III Orff certification in 2007 and has been integrating Orff methodology into her classroom teaching. She has been a director of two Aboriginal children&rsquo;s choirs in Edmonton. Sherryl is also a member of the highly successful Aboriginal trio, Asani, who received a 2006 Juno-nomination and she has recently released her debut solo album, Splashing the Water Loud-ly, which received a 2015 Indigenous Music Awards nomination for Best Indigenous Language or Francophone CD. She is a composer of children&rsquo;s drum songs and composed the theme song and Indigenous arts program, All My Relations: Celebrat-ing Canada&rsquo;s Indigenous Peoples &ndash; Teacher Guide for the National Arts Centre&rsquo;s Music Alive Program.</p>','','full_html'),('node','bio',0,331,331,'und',0,'<p>The clinicians include spoken word poet, <strong>Jillian Christmas</strong> who will lead the students in creating slam poetry. Jillian is co-director of Verses Festival of Words. She has facilitat-ed spoken word workshops for youth and adults across the country and is currently the Slam Master of the Vancouver Poetry Slam. Other clinicians include <strong>Faith Veikle</strong>, past president of the BC Orff Chapter and current president <strong>Sonja Karlson</strong>.</p>','','full_html'),('node','workshop',0,336,336,'und',0,'<p>The first part of the workshop will introduce different games, circle dances, songs and body percus-sion patterns. Each one will feature a combination of music, dance and voice. In the second half we will be part of a creative process with interlocking relationships. The steps of the process will build upon each other. We will start with one idea, the idea of interlocking. Pictures of interlocking patterns and forms will give the foundation for an improvisation with ropes and sounds. From pictures to improvisation, from single lines to an interlocking sculpture and from frozen bodies to a moving image. At the end of the process we will have group pieces to present.</p>','','full_html'),('node','workshop',0,346,346,'und',0,'<p>In the morning, join cultural singer, Sherryl Sewepagaham, in an interactive workshop learning and playing First Nations drum songs. We will explore tradi-tional hide drums, rattles, and sticks and their history and protocol as we sing and explore various traditional and contemporary songs and rhythms. A stick game will also be intro-duced to add to the experience. In the afternoon, Sherryl will lead an interactive exploration, improvisa-tion, and creation process with musical instruments working with Canadian First Nations legends. Help bring legend characters and stories to life with percussive and musical sounds and movement as we jour-ney into the teachings and life lessons that legends bring.</p>','','full_html'),('node','workshop',0,351,351,'und',0,'<p>BC Orff Chapter Members are invited to bring a group of up to 10 students from your school in grades 4 or 5 and observe the kids working with local master teachers through the Orff Process. Students will rotate through stations developing instrument, movement and vocal skills. At the end of the day, there will be a per-formance for parents.</p>','','full_html');
